Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Alex, thanks for doing this.

I wonder if this is the right time to fix the py35 gate and get the other tests working on the same.

I see invocation error for this test on the gate and puts the verification in question.

http://logs.openstack.org/61/436161/1/check/gate-glance-python35-nv/aa5d3b0/console.html#_2017-02-20_19_46_25_683176

Patch Set 1:

Nikhil, the invocation error is unrelated to this change. It's actually due to a failing scrubber test, which will be fixed by this patch: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/435585/

I don't quite follow the meaning of your comment. Are you wondering if it's the right "time" to make any py35 fixes. Or if it's the right time to fix "all" of the tests? I've been slowly working towards the latter goal. So that instead of calling out individual tests in the py35 job using 'python -m testtools.run', we can just run 'ostestr' as we do in the py27 job.
Topic changed from py35/enable-test_api to goal-python35/enable-test_api
Topic changed from goal-python35/enable-test_api to goal-python35/glance

Let's get the dependency merged in and put a recheck on this patch so that debugging is easier.
